  "body": "According to code snippet https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/e633a1604f00908a1dcc898b206c3404db4d82ed/pkg/controller/service/service_controller.go#L263-L290\r\n\r\nThe `createLoadBalancerIfNeeded` handles the **ServiceUpdate** events, it first check out whether or not current service need a LoadBalancer, and if not, it ensures corresponding LoadBalacner deleted.  \r\n\r\nHowever, another branch of the `if` statement is a little bit confusing. It says _The load balancer doesn't exist yet, so create it_, and then it calls `s.createLoadBalancer`. I think at this time, we're not sure whether or not the load balancer already exists (since we didn't call `GetLoadBalancer`), so the proper behavior would be *ensure load balancer exists* (actually `s.createLoadBalancer` just calls `EnsureLoadBalancer` indeed), so the comment (L-283) and the function name (L-285 `createLoadBalancer`) isn't very appropriate, it's confusing right?",
